////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Compound of Five Tetrahedra as Excavated Dodecahedron
//
// Matthew Arcus, 2020
//
// Take an icosahedral kaleidoscope (using precalculated values), and
// take slices through the fundamental region with planes through the
// vertices of a dodecahedron. The result is a great range of shapes -
// stellations, facetings and other more irregular but pretty shapes.
//
// Here we see the compound of five tetrahedra as a chiral excavation.
//
// <mouse>: rotation
// <up>/<down>: move in/out
// c: clip at x=0
// r: autorotation
// 
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

bool dorotate = true;
